<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="25" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="25">
Pfeiffer did not state on how many specimens his description was based; only a single specimen was found. 
<bibRefCitation author="Muratov, IV" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Conchology" pageId="48" pageNumber="65" pagination="611 - 615" refId="B58" refString="Muratov, IV, Gargominy, O, 2011. Taxonomic position of the land snail Bulimus demerarensis L. Pfeiffer 1861 (Gastropoda, Pulmonata, Bulimulidae). Journal of Conchology 40: 611 - 615" title="Taxonomic position of the land snail Bulimus demerarensis L. Pfeiffer 1861 (Gastropoda, Pulmonata, Bulimulidae)." volume="40" year="2011">Muratov and Gargominy (2011)</bibRefCitation>
re-described this taxon and studied the anatomy of a single dried individual. They concluded that this taxon &quot;lacks the very characteristic, for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Albers" authorityYear="1850" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Leiostracus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leiostracus" order="Pulmonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Leiostracus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, division of the spermathecal duct into an enlarged distal part and a slender proximal part that connect to the distal part sub-apically, which is essentially the only character that separates 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Albers" authorityYear="1850" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Leiostracus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leiostracus" order="Pulmonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Leiostracus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Troschel, 1847 sensu Breure 1979 (see also Breure" authorityYear="2012" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bostryx" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bostryx" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Bostryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;. As 
<bibRefCitation author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 255" refId="B9" refString="Breure, ASH, 1978. Notes on and descriptions of Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden 164: 1 - 255" title="Notes on and descriptions of Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda)." volume="164" year="1978">Breure (1978</bibRefCitation>
: 239-240) has shown, these two genera also differ in their radula structure, which was not studied by Muratov and Gargominy. Moreover, molecular data lends support for clear differentiation of both genera, even in different families (
<bibRefCitation author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fuer Molluskenkunde" pageId="46" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 20" publicationUrl="10.1127/arch.moll/1869-0963/141/001-020" refId="B17" refString="Breure, ASH, Romero, PE, 2012. Support and surprises: molecular phylogeny of the land snail superfamily Orthalicoidea using a three-locus gene analysis with divergence time analysis and ancestral area reconstruction. Archiv fuer Molluskenkunde 141: 1 - 20, DOI: 10.1127/arch.moll/1869-0963/141/001-020" title="Support and surprises: molecular phylogeny of the land snail superfamily Orthalicoidea using a three-locus gene analysis with divergence time analysis and ancestral area reconstruction." url="10.1127/arch.moll/1869-0963/141/001-020" volume="141" year="2012">Breure and Romero 2012</bibRefCitation>
); more research may be needed to ascertain the position of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pfeiffer’s">Pfeiffer's</normalizedToken>
taxon. The generic classification of 
<bibRefCitation author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 215" refId="B10" refString="Breure, ASH, 1979. Systematics, phylogeny and zoogeography of Bulimulinae (Mollusca). Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden 168: 1 - 215" title="Systematics, phylogeny and zoogeography of Bulimulinae (Mollusca)." volume="168" year="1979">Breure (1979)</bibRefCitation>
is retained herein.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
